The paper discusses the challenges of implementing the fast multipole method (FMM) on current parallel computers and future exascale architectures, with a focus on inter-node communication. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the FMM is a numerical method used in scientific computing, which could place the paper in the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of the FMM, which could place it in the Performance (cs.SC) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper discusses the FMM's application to preconditioners for sparse linear solvers, which could place it in the Mathematical Software (cs.MS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of implementing the FMM on future exascale architectures, which could place it in the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
